</div>Yes yes, run in your gerbil wheel, its sooooo exciting. Who said anything about raid content? How about, gee, I dunno, 5 mans that don't suck balls and have new content that's interesting and fun? How about a gearing scheme that doesn't involve running a lamely designed 5-man 30 times, then going back to do it again on heroik. Why do I like my raid gear? It took a brain to get it. Something I can't say about anything that I got questing in BC. <br />
<br />
And maybe, this may sound crazy, put the loot that is a full notch above the rest in these interesting 5 mans, as opposed to dropping it like candy for the ADD kiddies while they run around and stab things, who get all red in the face when they aren't fed gear with ever bigger numbers on a steady diet while they put out a minimum effort of grinding retardedly easy quests, dry humping the next 10 levels because that's the only metric of entertainment they can deal with. <br />
<br />
And this is coming from someone who got as far as Molten Core before BC came out. I don't want to preserve my l33tness, I just want a gear scale that doesn't feel like ****ing Diablo, planned worse. I'm sick of generic trash loot, where you get duplicate items with different names, where there is so much loot they've even managed to screw up making tier pieces the equivalent of blues, because they are churning it out in droves so you, I guess, can feel all big and heroic.  <br />
<br />
But don't worry Darth. You're getting your gerbil wheel, complete with your pellets to keep you happy while you jog. An expansion without levels would tell me that Blizz is serious about designing content, instead of designing the next carrot (Level Cap) to dangle in front of you to keep you playing.</div>
