</div>That's not the issue, but thanks for taking the easy shot. Fact is I've seen Karazhan and Gruuls Lair since BC came out, and have been doing Karazhan for months. That's all. But if that is hardcore to you, well, whatever. I could care less what you're wearing. What I do care about is that the laziness and need for instant gratification by some of the player base ends up creating an ever increasing scale of lame gear, that is 3ap, 1 hit, and 1 stat better than the piece before it, or what have you. Everything is incremental, essentially duplicated, and boring. And the means of getting this fantastically lame gear also becomes boring, and duplicated. <br />
<br />
<div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
