</div>Oh I agree the Arena system and its gear is broke, but at least you have to do the arenas to get it. I count that as more effort than mowing through a few hundred redundant quests and having gear handed to you for killing 10 of something. A macro can be as successful. <br />
<br />
What I find ironic is that you trot out the e-peen criticism when that's essentially your argument for why you want to have the next tier of gear handed to you on a silver platter. You want to feel geared playing on your minimum, non-raiding play time. Which I can understand. Except its dictating the entire loot scale for everyone else, because you're asking for a lowest common denominator way of designing gear and giving it out. Which is why there are now 3 raid instances required just to even see BT. Considering you probably won't even try to see the other content out there, I think that's pretty unfair to the people that are actually playing the larger portion of the game.</div>
