</div>I guess you and I just see the questing different. I see it as the same game with a different name. Instead of &quot;Gorlock Invasion&quot; where you slay 10 Gorlock Ogres, now its &quot;Feralfen Revenge&quot; where you kill 10 feral fens. The questing to me is a grind because its so very, very easy, and so very, very simple. And you just do it, ad nauseam, for 10 levels. &quot;Succeeding&quot; is about as tough and interesting as &quot;farming&quot;. Azeroth quests at least had some variety to them. With the exception of the bombing runs, I'm hard pressed to think of more than a few quests that break from the same march of uncreative ideas and tasks. So the prospect of another 10 levels of what I saw in BC is.....depressing. <br />
<br />
As for the Arena gear....I don't really care. I don't do arenas, and what other people get doesn't really matter to me. What does matter to me is knowing the content I will be doing seems to be designed for people who just want to be shoveled easy xp, gold, and items. You might be entertained by it, but it bores me to tears.</div>
