    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_403488">Well there we go then.<br />
<br />
Basically, I prefer it the way they do it now, because it caters to both of us.  Yes, your forced to play content you don't like to get to the raid content you do enjoy.  That sucks for you I guess.<br />
<br />
On the otherhand, if they did it the way you wanted, my content wouldn't even exist.  I'd basically be screwed because they'd only be adding new raid content like half the EQ expansions do.<br />
<br />
So I think, all things considered the &quot;you have to play a couple months of stuff you don't wanna before you can play the stuff you do wanna&quot; is better for everyone than the &quot;the stuff I don't wanna play is all there is, because the stuff I wanna play isn't even in the game.&quot;<br />
<br />
Ideally, you'd be able to just raid your way to 80 and not have to do quests at all.  But really, whats a dungeon really besides just a 5 man raid?</div>
